window.docContents[170].resolve({"/Analytic-Number-Theory/Forthcoming-in-mathlib/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Analytic-Number-Theory--Forthcoming-in-mathlib":{"contents":"The nodes below are informal statements of results that are the subject of open mathlib pull\nrequests (the t-number-theory queue). Each carries a pr_url pointing at the live PR and no\n(lean := …) reference: the declarations are not yet in mathlib v4.30.0-rc2. They connect into the\ndependency graph through the mathlib-backed nodes of this chapter (and, for the modular -series,\nthe Modular Forms chapter), and should be re-pointed to (lean := …) once the corresponding PR merges.\n\n\n\n\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Analytic Number Theory","header":"2.14. Forthcoming in mathlib","id":"/Analytic-Number-Theory/Forthcoming-in-mathlib/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Analytic-Number-Theory--Forthcoming-in-mathlib"},"/Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory/Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory--Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings--Localization-at-a-Prime-Produces-a-Discrete-Valuation-Ring":{"contents":"Let  be a Dedekind domain (or any domain with a height-one prime) and  a nonzero\nprime of . The localisation  is a discrete valuation ring, with the\n-adic valuation as its discrete valuation. Completing at  produces a\ncomplete discrete valuation ring whose fraction field is a local field\n(); for a number field this completion is a mixed characteristic local field.\nFormalised in LocalClassFieldTheory: discreteValuationRing — sorry-free.\n\nThe -adic valuation on  is discrete, and localising at  makes its\nunit ball the local ring , which the project establishes is a discrete valuation\nring (Localization.discreteValuationRing). Completing  in the\n-adic metric preserves the discrete valuation and the residue field while making the\nring complete (the completion file). When  is the ring of integers of a number\nfield, the residue field  is finite and the fraction field of the completion has\ncharacteristic , so it is a mixed characteristic local field by definition\n().\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Class Field Theory and Galois Theory\u0009Local fields and complete discrete valuation rings","header":"4.5.3. Localization at a Prime Produces a Discrete Valuation Ring","id":"/Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory/Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory--Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings--Localization-at-a-Prime-Produces-a-Discrete-Valuation-Ring"},"/Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms/Dimension-formula-for-level-one-modular-forms/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms--Dimension-formula-for-level-one-modular-forms--Vanishing-of-cusp-forms-below-weight-twelve":{"contents":"For , the space  is zero.\n\nThe discriminant isomorphism () identifies  with , and\nfor  the weight  is negative. Level-one modular forms of negative weight vanish\n(), so  and hence .\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Modular and Automorphic Forms\u0009Dimension formula for level-one modular forms","header":"6.7.3. Vanishing of cusp forms below weight twelve","id":"/Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms/Dimension-formula-for-level-one-modular-forms/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms--Dimension-formula-for-level-one-modular-forms--Vanishing-of-cusp-forms-below-weight-twelve"}});